cs.MM, cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.IT, cs.NI 

The paper discusses a new representation and coding technique for interactive multiview streaming systems, which involves multimedia applications, image and video processing, and networking. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.MM (Multimedia), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.GR (Graphics). The paper also deals with bandwidth and storage constraints, which are related to information theory and networking, making cs.IT (Information Theory) a likely category as well. Finally, the paper proposes a method to optimize the partitioning of the navigation domain, which involves optimization and algorithms, making cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) a possible category.
